casebody.data:
STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
Alan L. ESTES, II, Appellant. WD 81871 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: June 25, 2019 Eric S. Schmitt, Attorney General, and Richard A. Starnes, Assistant Attorney General, Jefferson City, MO, Attorneys for Respondent. F.A. White, Jr., and Blade Moore, Kansas City, MO, Attorneys for Appellant. Before Division Four: Karen King Mitchell, Chief Judge, and Alok Ahuja and Cynthia L. Martin, Judges

Order

Per Curiam:

Alan Estes appeals, following a bench trial, his convictions of attempted enticement of a child, § 566.151, and attempted first-degree sodomy, § 566.060, for which he was sentenced to consecutive terms of six years' imprisonment on each count. Estes raises two claims on appeal, challenging the sufficiency of the evidence to support each conviction. Finding no error, we affirm. Rule 30.25(b).
